Depp was likely following the advice of Greg Ellis (referring here to the stated slow leak of negative info. re: Amber), a co-star and supporter of Depp.

Ellis was helping Depp, via assistance with tactics aimed to take down the “feminists” and the “Family Law

No emotional empathy
Sense of Entitlement 
Hyper-sensitivity to sense of control
No accountability / Blame shifting
Think in black and white, no compromises or shades of grey
Use Triangulation, objects and people, as a way of asserting control and manipulating
No boundary recognition

Dishonesty and lies to achieve control & fuel, ie positive and/or negative emotional responses
Future faking and re-writing history

comment:
I really have never liked Johnny Depp movies. I followed this link out of curiosity. I remember watching a movie "Men Don't Tell" where a husband was beaten by his wife.From the text of the call, it seems that Amber was relying on that same premise. That society doesn't believe it when a man claims abuse.  It was pretty sad hearing him chain smoking away while she rants about her integrity and how bad everything is for her. She was still abusing him in this call. She didn't even have the decency to confirm that his son was being harmed by the things going on it was just "What about me???My friends??? Family???"

But I still wonder...Was this a setup so we could hear how vile she is and he could seem so calm?  Why tape the call? He is much smarter than she seems to be and less overtly unstable. Having just filed something in court he probably knew she would call to rant. I heard two parts where there was real emotion in his voice and not just some kind of resigned acceptance. (1) about his integrity and (2) about his son. Did he outwit her here? Was he giving her a last chance before she destroyed herself? I think the two times that there was emotion in his voice probably reveals why he would let her destroy herself. How can you not allow that happen to someone that would besmirch your name and harm your children without a qualm?

comment:
I've been in a relationship with someone this toxic..

I will never forget when my ex (year long relationship) accused me of cheating when I'd didn't. At 24 years old I was working every day and night to pay the bills and was getting 3 hours of sleep every night from working 3 jobs. She was going to school and living off of my income. I got tired of it and I said "if you're going to falsely accuse me of always cheating than I might as well do it anyways".

She pulled a knife on me in my own kitchen and told me I wouldn't live to tell the story. She even asked me "even if I was to stab you in 'self defense' who do you think the cops would believe you as a man or me?". She even started fake crying with a knife pointed at my stomach while I was doing dishes and started talking to me as if she was speaking to cops afterwards.. saying things  in a sobbing voice like "he was coming at me and I didn't know what to do".

I then planned my escape that weekend afterwards, and moved out.. bought a gun (carry it on me 24/7) and have never looked back. But all I remember thinking all the time is there's women out there who are this crazy, abusive and hide that they think this way. They will hurt or threaten anyone to get what they want.

Still to this day my current wife tells me I have issues trusting people (like friends and family). We even reflected and it took me about a year or two to properly fall asleep overnight in the same bed together since we've started. I always tell her you would too after what I've dealt with.

comment:
Reality doesnt magically bend into the ficticious story that chronic liars make up in their heads. They don't get that. Reality is Reality. Amber Heard is the one who fucked up her OWN Reputation when she put on bruise makeup (or punched herself) and walked into the Courthouse in *full view* for the Paparazzi, in orderto file for a restraining order from her own goddamned husband!? 
SHE DID THAT. She purged herself to the Law and now she faces 3yrs in jail for that. As a result she's uninsurable for the movies she wanted to do and you know how I feel about that? Boo the fuck hoo.

All she cares about is her Reputation? Well, Amber Heard, whom I only just heard of this month, you are a garbage person. Get the fuck over it! (Preferably in prison) 🙃🙃🙃

 She didn't have bruises any other day after the supposed "incident", just the day she went to file! 🤕😖

If she were a real victim (which she proved by her own "evidence" that she is not 😂) then the cops she had called that fateful night in her posh Depp-supplied apartment, mightve seen something. Their report says the opposite, there wasn't anything to be seen!
One (a Domestic Abuse Detective) most definitely would have seen a SHRED of evidence of Domestic Abuse, if there was any. 
Like damage to Amber, whom they inspected, or the apartments, or the hallways, when they arrived within minutes of the call.

But they did not see shit. All they had was her remaining silent, rejecting giving a statement, etc..
And now she has the gall to say THEY LIED and THEY DIDN'T DO THEIR JOBS??! 
Way to piss off the cops in your precinct, dummy!

If she was a true victim don't you think there would have been, you know, some external PROOF? 

I know a narcissist just like her in my family. She'd rather trash my name in a lie she told to make herself feel better. Going on 20yrs now she STILL can't come clean about it!? We grew up tight, too. I think she'd rather die than admit she lied, knowing full well that most people don't even believe her! Doctors need to look into these peopl, hardcore. They skew what reality looks like into something unrecognizable.

I have another 2 known pervasive hurtful narcissists in my past that I wish I had never crossed paths with. People need to know the symptoms of this cancerous behavior and run the fuck away from these guys and girls ASAP!

I'm proud of Johnny. He brought this to light for alot of other men to bring up their narcissistic exes abuse. My husband was abused from his ex-wife and he still suffers from that.

The social investigation is closed and the investigator met 4 different personalities from my husband's ex-wife. He fully believed that she was bipolar narcasisst and he needed to have full custody of his daughter. 
Johnny you won't believe what and how many doors you have opened for other men and courts to see how women like this actually exist.

Amber your career is going to come crashing down. I will personally NEVER watch an Aquaman movie with you in it. We actually got you to not be in the next Aquaman movie. 
I stand with Johnny and I am behind him 100%. 
Any movie you are in, TV show, even if you are a guest on a talk show I will boycott every single thing you will appear in. You are a disgusting disgrace of a woman!

comment: As a domestic violence survivor I want to point out a couple of obvious red flags that completely, in my mind, prove Johnny did not abuse her.  One is she said she had 3 years of "evidence" which includes texts, pictures, and statements.  That's not evidence, that was a planned set up.  And two, someone who is being or has been abused would never get away with raising their voice to the abuser nonetheless be allowed to argue for 30 minutes.   She is so disconnected with what an actual victim of abuse experiences, she couldn't even act the part.  As a side note, an abuser leaves a trail of victims behind them and every woman from his previous relationships have supported him.  That speaks volumes.   The media who jumped on Amber's lies has a responsibility to make things right.  And all those people who boycotted him and damaged his career without fact, need to admit their error and now throw as much energy, if not more, to bring down the actual abuser.

comment: I feel sooo bad for him.  I know first-hand how seductive and addictive it can be being someone’s most favorite person in the world, but unfortunately there’s a flip-side to that coin.  For most of us, the way we feel about someone changes very slowly; we are not constantly shifting back and forth from one extreme to the next, at the mercy of our emotions.  When we love someone, we still love them even when they are being jerks.  I can’t understand what it feels like to be borderline, but I’ve heard that it’s a much worse hell than what they put us through.  I’ve heard that, but I still find it really hard to believe, because when nothing is ever your fault, then you’re basically living in a fantasy world of your own making...but perhaps it’s still too fresh for me.  I’ve heard that bpd is profoundly lonely...even when they have unconditional love from someone like Johnny, they still feel alone and empty, because they are incapable of filling up their own empty love well.  But still, having loved someone like that, it takes a serious toll on your health and sanity, and it’s nearly killed me,...I really feel it has triggered a cascading chain of events in my body.  You are never the same after something like this, or so I’ve heard.  But we can recover.  I’m feeling hope that I can heal my body by removing this huge source of trauma from my life, and by putting my own needs first.  We can only save ourselves.  I’m rooting for Johnny.  He is not alone.  I’m sorry if I’ve diagnosed Amber incorrectly.  Is anyone else recognizing BPD here, or am I being presumptuous?
